# Almaly, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Almaly (; , AlmalÄ±) is a rural locality (a village) in Petrovsky Selsoviet, Ishimbaysky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 73 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Almaly is located 45 km northeast of Ishimbay (the district's administrative centre) by road. Vasilyevka is the nearest rural locality.
